Swansea City striker Andre Ayew is being linked with a surprise return to Ligue 1 giants Marseille. The forward started his career with the French giants and is now being linked with a return to the club, just four years after he left them to join Swansea. Powered by RubiQube Ad Network Despite scoring twice after coming on as a substitute in Swansea’s 3-1 Carabao Cup triumph against Northampton Town last night, Ayew, according to Ghana Web , could return to the Stade Vélodrome by the end of the European window.